pan><hr size=1> Here's my leet strat<br>
<br>
Version 1<br>
<br>
Using 61 air, BO V, Flameshield of Ro<br>
Pull with malosini <br>
Open with heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
etc..<br>
<br>
Version 2<br>
<br>
Using 61 air, BO V, Flameshield of Ro<br>
Pull with boots of bladecalling<br>
Open with Malosini<br>
Heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
Firebolt of Tallon<br>
Heal<br>
<br>
Fights take 30%-55% of my mana per kill.<br>
<br>
Occaisionally I will step in to take a few hits, just like I did in my 20s.<br>
<br>
btw the purpose of openning with the heals or malosini is to let the pet build aggro.  You do not want to just sit there doing nothing at the beginning of the fight while you wait for your pet to get aggro.  Even if your heal won't land for full, cast it anyway. <p><center><br>
<font = "arial" size = 3>Goladus Mistrydia<br>
<a href = "http://www.darkblood.com">Darkblood</a></font><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=317634"><font = "arial" size = 1>(profile)</font></a>
</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=goladus>Goladus</A> at: 2/15/03 7:16:33 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2911<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 7:11:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Solo mage in POP</span><hr size=1> Soloing trees and spiders in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>PoN</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Yoyo Rooting</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>57 Greater Vocaration: Earth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Since the pet can't tank, I don't let it.  I use it only to root.  I alternate <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>/pet attack, /pet hold</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> until it roots it, nuke, and repeat.<br>
<br>
Think of it as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;mage ghetto slow.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  Who cares how much damage the mobs deal if they never get within melee range of anything?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 292<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 7:35:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Use enrage</span><hr size=1> If you're 62, you should try to get Sun Storm. That will give you some great damage output together with FBoT. Also try to get the 61 air pet, it tanks just better than the 62 water pet (and the stun helps to avoid damage too).<br>
<br>
Then you can try this:<br>
- get pet ready<br>
- pull a mob (best Malosini to pull)<br>
- almost immediately start off with Sun Storm (perhaps wait until the pet has stunned or taunted once), and rotate between Firebolt and SunStorm until mob runs or is dead.<br>
<br>
The tricky parts: You have to watch aggro very closely (I would love to see how spell casting subtlety works here). Your air pet will usually get aggro back quickly so if you do too much just run around a few circles. Usually if you switch between bolt and rain, you can avoid aggro. Also note that your pet wont last long. You will usually come to the point where your pet ENRAGES. This is GOOD, use it! Enrage gives you about 10 sec more time to finish off a mob. Do another bolt when you see enrage, you want quick damage now. Mob should be dead or running now.<br>
When finished reclaim pet (I think this is the best thing to do since pets only enrage once in their life from what I've heard, cant confirm this yet). Canni or med up, and repeat <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
This works well in PoN on treants, ravens and spiders. Should also work in other first tier zones without problems.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 941<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 10:05:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Use enrage</span><hr size=1> I've done solo in PoN in a couple different ways.<br>
<br>
Regular chaining of 61 Air pet works, but you need a good sized mana pool, or KEI.<br>
<br>
I can regular chain the mobs down to about 30%, then I can reclaim chain them down a bit below that, then cast a single FoT to finish them off.  Canni mana back, repeat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1xtro1>1xtro1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 10:54:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Use enrage</span><hr size=1> Try argo kiting. Pull with bolt and run in circle with water pet with it's sow. Once pet takes argo do it again with bolt till you got argo. Leave pet taunt off. I did this type of soloing in sky fire back when my mana pool and pet health wasn't enough to kill the mob. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:times new roman;font-size:x-small;">Xtro Humongus<br>
Mythrilmoon Mystics<br>
Don of the Mage Mafia</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123199">My Crap</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2915<br> <font color=#333333>(2/15/03 4:47:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=196.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Use enrage</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> did this type of soloing in sky fire back when my mana pool and pet health wasn't enough to kill the mob.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Tried aggro kiting, never got the hang of it.  Not really my style, either.<br>
